# RDPD - question 21-25
1. What does the phrase “talk until I was blue in the face” in page 21 mean?
The phrase means to keep talking endlessly without receiving any result . 
Reference : "I could talk until I was blue in the face, but you wouldn’t hear a thing."
2. How did the rich dad teach the boys the first lesson about life?
* He made them:
- Work in his store for very low pay (~ 10 cents per hour). Then later for no pay at all, So they could feel tired of working for money and start thinking for themselves.
Reference : “I decided to design a course that mirrored real life… So I decided to let life push you around a bit… That’s why I only paid you 10 cents.” (pt.34
! Advance reference : Desktop image
3. According to rich dad, is fear a part of true learning? Provide evidence
Yes, He said fear is a primary part of true learning.
Reference : “True learning takes energy, passion… When it comes to money, most people want to play it safe… Fear does.” (pt.36)
4. According to rich dad, why do most people learn to work for money?
Because fear controls them 
Reference : it’s fear that keeps most people working at a job: the fearof not paying their bills, the fear of being fired, the fear of not having enough money, and the fear of starting over.(pt.37 )
5. What kind of questions did rich dad ask the author in page 24?
Reflective question to make the boy reconsider about what he said 
Reference : From the question :"So what are you learning" (pt.35)
6. What kind of answers did the rich dad give to the author in page 25?
Rich dad give them those reality-base
Reference : He told the boys that if they till blaming him, they wont recveive any lesson
“If you think I’m the problem, then you have to change me. If you realize that you’re the problem, then you can change yourself…” (pt.35)
